  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Frontline Health Workers Fighting NCDs: IntraHealth International &amp; Medtronic Foundation Advocacy Partnership</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award will be used to: continue development and dissemination of the evidence base for the critical role of frontline health workers in addressing NCDs; to highlight the case at key global gatherings for greater utilization of frontline health workers to fight diabetes and cardiovascular disease; and to continue the use and expansion of storytelling training for frontline health workers tackling NCDs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant supports advocacy for increased global attention to frontline health workers as essential to resilient and responsive health systems and critical in managing and controlling acute and chronic noncommunicable diseases (NCDs) in low- and middle-income countries.</narrative>
  </description>
